# Format URLs as Markdown Links

When outputting URLs in chat responses, always use markdown link syntax so they are clickable in the Cursor chat view.

## Examples

### Good

```
Created PR: [#125862](https://github.com/VantaInc/obsidian/pull/125862)

See the [JIRA ticket](https://vanta.atlassian.net/browse/AIPLAT-106) for details.

[Test recording](https://www.loom.com/share/fb9c10cd1dc44af9a4353bb7919eff3a)
```

### Bad

```
Created PR: https://github.com/VantaInc/obsidian/pull/125862

See the JIRA ticket at https://vanta.atlassian.net/browse/AIPLAT-106

Test recording: https://www.loom.com/share/fb9c10cd1dc44af9a4353bb7919eff3a
```

## Rationale

Raw URLs are not clickable in Cursor's chat view. Markdown link syntax `[text](url)` renders as clickable links, improving usability.
